@startuml
!define AWSPUML https://raw.githubusercontent.com/awslabs/aws-icons-for-plantuml/v14.0/dist
skinparam participantPadding 20
skinparam boxPadding 10

actor User
participant "Frontend\n(S3 Static Web)" as Frontend
participant "API Gateway" as APIGW
participant "Cognito" as Cognito
participant "Lambda:\nstandings" as LambdaStandings
participant "Lambda:\npredictions" as LambdaPredictions
participant "Lambda:\ngetFixtures" as LambdaGetFixtures
participant "Lambda:\ngetScore" as LambdaGetScore
participant "Lambda:\ngetLiveScores" as LambdaGetLiveScores
participant "Lambda:\nLF1" as LambdaLF1
participant "Lambda:\nLF2" as LambdaLF2
participant "Lambda:\nscrapeMatchData" as LambdaScrape
participant "DynamoDB" as DynamoDB
participant "ElasticSearch" as ES
participant "SageMaker" as SageMaker
participant "Lex" as Lex
participant "SQS" as SQS
participant "SNS" as SNS
participant "S3 Bucket" as S3
participant "Kafka\n(EC2)" as Kafka
participant "Football API" as FootballAPI

== User Authentication ==
User -> Frontend: Access Application
Frontend -> Cognito: Authenticate User
Cognito --> Frontend: Return Auth Token
Frontend --> User: Display Dashboard

== View Standings ==
User -> Frontend: Request Standings
Frontend -> APIGW: GET /standings
APIGW -> LambdaStandings: Invoke
activate LambdaStandings
LambdaStandings -> DynamoDB: Query Standings Table
DynamoDB --> LambdaStandings: Return Standings Data
LambdaStandings --> APIGW: Return Response
deactivate LambdaStandings
APIGW --> Frontend: Standings Data
Frontend --> User: Display Standings

== Match Predictions ==
User -> Frontend: Request Match Prediction
Frontend -> APIGW: GET /predictions
APIGW -> LambdaPredictions: Invoke
activate LambdaPredictions
LambdaPredictions -> SageMaker: Invoke ML Model
SageMaker --> LambdaPredictions: Return Prediction Results
LambdaPredictions --> APIGW: Return Predictions
deactivate LambdaPredictions
APIGW --> Frontend: Prediction Data
Frontend --> User: Display Predictions

== Get Fixtures ==
User -> Frontend: Request Fixtures
Frontend -> APIGW: GET /fixtures?dateRange
APIGW -> LambdaGetFixtures: Invoke
activate LambdaGetFixtures
LambdaGetFixtures -> ES: Query Fixtures by Date Range
ES --> LambdaGetFixtures: Return Fixture Data
LambdaGetFixtures --> APIGW: Return Fixtures
deactivate LambdaGetFixtures
APIGW --> Frontend: Fixture Data
Frontend --> User: Display Fixtures

== View Live Scores ==
User -> Frontend: Request Live Scores
Frontend -> APIGW: GET /liveScores
APIGW -> LambdaGetLiveScores: Invoke
activate LambdaGetLiveScores
LambdaGetLiveScores -> DynamoDB: Query Live Scores Table
DynamoDB --> LambdaGetLiveScores: Return Live Score Data
LambdaGetLiveScores --> APIGW: Return Scores
deactivate LambdaGetLiveScores
APIGW --> Frontend: Live Score Data
Frontend --> User: Display Live Scores

== Get Match Score Details ==
User -> Frontend: Request Specific Match Score
Frontend -> APIGW: GET /score?matchId
APIGW -> LambdaGetScore: Invoke
activate LambdaGetScore
LambdaGetScore -> ES: Query Match Data
ES --> LambdaGetScore: Return Match Info
LambdaGetScore -> DynamoDB: Query Score Details
DynamoDB --> LambdaGetScore: Return Score Data
LambdaGetScore --> APIGW: Return Complete Score
deactivate LambdaGetScore
APIGW --> Frontend: Score Data
Frontend --> User: Display Score Details

== Chatbot Interaction (Direct) ==
User -> Frontend: Open Chatbot
Frontend -> Lex: Send User Message
Lex -> LambdaLF1: Process Intent
activate LambdaLF1
alt Greeting Intent
    LambdaLF1 --> Lex: Return Greeting Response
else Fixtures Intent
    LambdaLF1 -> ES: Query Fixtures
    ES --> LambdaLF1: Return Fixtures
    LambdaLF1 --> Lex: Return Fixtures Response
else Results Intent
    LambdaLF1 -> DynamoDB: Query Results
    DynamoDB --> LambdaLF1: Return Results
    LambdaLF1 --> Lex: Return Results Response
else Recommendations Intent
    LambdaLF1 --> Lex: Return Recommendations
else Uber Integration Intent
    LambdaLF1 --> Lex: Return Uber Info
end
deactivate LambdaLF1
Lex --> Frontend: Chatbot Response
Frontend --> User: Display Response

== Chatbot Interaction (Async via Queue) ==
User -> Frontend: Request Fixture Notification
Frontend -> Lex: Send Request
Lex -> SQS: Enqueue Request
SQS --> Lex: Acknowledge
Lex --> Frontend: Request Queued
Frontend --> User: Confirmation Message

LambdaLF2 -> SQS: Poll Queue
activate LambdaLF2
SQS --> LambdaLF2: Return Message
LambdaLF2 -> ES: Query Fixtures by Date Range
ES --> LambdaLF2: Return Fixture Data
LambdaLF2 -> SNS: Send SMS Notification
SNS --> LambdaLF2: SMS Sent Confirmation
LambdaLF2 -> SQS: Delete Message
deactivate LambdaLF2

== Live Score Updates via Kafka ==
FootballAPI -> Kafka: Fetch Live Data
activate Kafka
note right: producer.js fetches\nand publishes
Kafka -> Kafka: Serialize with Avro
Kafka -> Kafka: Publish to Topic
Kafka -> Kafka: Consumer Reads Topic
note right: consumer.js processes
Kafka -> Kafka: Deserialize with Avro
Kafka -> DynamoDB: Store/Update Live Scores
deactivate Kafka

== Match Data Scraping ==
FootballAPI -> S3: Upload Match Data JSON
S3 -> LambdaScrape: Trigger S3 Event
activate LambdaScrape
LambdaScrape -> S3: Read JSON File
S3 --> LambdaScrape: Return JSON Data
LambdaScrape -> LambdaScrape: Parse Match Standings
LambdaScrape -> DynamoDB: Store Standings Data
DynamoDB --> LambdaScrape: Confirm Write
deactivate LambdaScrape

@enduml
